nd"}]},{"type":"text","value":", at Southampton Arts Center, 2022  "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://techspressionism.com/exhibition/southampton/michael-paulukonis/","rel":["noopener","noreferer"],"target":"_blank"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"https://techspressionism.com/exhibition/southampton/michael-paulukonis/"}]}]}]}],"toc":{"title":"","searchDepth":2,"depth":2,"links":[{"id":"places-i-can-or-have-been-found","depth":2,"text":"Places I can or have been found"}]}},"_type":"markdown","_id":"content:blog:publications.md","_source":"content","_file":"blog/publications.md","_stem":"blog/publications","_extension":"md"},{"_path":"/blog/watmap","_dir":"blog","_draft":false,"_partial":false,"_locale":"","title":"WATMAP and other delights","description":"A glitch-aesthetic mosaic image-remaker built in Processing by somebody else","headline":"WATMAP and other delights","date":"2019-09-14","dateUpdated":"","author":"Michael Paulukonis","socialImage":{"src":"/blog/media/sample.webp","mime":"webp","alt":"Mountain","width":1200,"height":630},"tags":["art","processing","glitch","tools"],"body":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tag":"h1","props":{"id":"we-can-rebuild-it-for-you-wholesale"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"We can rebuild it for you wholesale!"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"img","props":{"alt":"My son reimagined via WATMAP","src":"/blog/media/watmap.00.png"},"children":[]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Processing2/3 code written by "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://github.com/tsulej/GenerateMe/tree/master/watmap","rel":["noopener","noreferer"],"target":"_blank"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"GenerateMe"}]},{"type":"text","value":". See their "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://generateme.tumblr.com/","rel":["noopener","noreferer"],"target":"_blank"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"TumblrBlog"}]},{"type":"text","value":" for use and tips."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"A "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"http://everythingability.com/","rel":["noopener","noreferer"],"target":"_blank"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"friend"}]},{"type":"text","value":" thinks of it a \"a poor-man's GAN\". I can see the similarities: an image is \"recreated\", using elements from something else."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Original developer refers to it as part of a \"glitch-aesthetic\" which I get - but it's not a glitch, an error. There are seeming \"hiccups\" in the discontinuities. It's essentially a tile-mosaic replicator using a quad-tree to focus on sizes. It takes a long time to process, mainly due to the quad-tree preocessing."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I thought that "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://www.instagram.com/richard.winters/","rel":["noopener","noreferer"],"target":"_blank"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Richard Winters"}]},{"type":"text","value":" (last time I checked, all images had been removed, which makes me sad) was using a custom version inspired by WATMAP, but I've long-since changed my mind. Using square-subsections (instead of variadic-sized rectangles) and processes each color channel (RGB?) separately. So, channel-based tile-sets."}]}],"toc":{"title":"","searchDepth":2,"depth":2,"links":[]}},"_type":"markdown","_id":"content:blog:watmap.md","_source":"content","_file":"blog/watmap.md","_stem":"blog/watmap","_extension":"md"}],"navigation":[{"title":"Authors","_path":"/authors"},{"title":"Blog","_path":"/blog","children":[{"title":"Automated Art Automatons","_path":"/blog/automated-bots"},{"title":"Daily Code Monas","_path":"/blog/daily-code-monas"},{"title":"A Nuxt blog using Content","_path":"/blog/nuxt-content-blog"},{"title"